RE: ACookFromNY's comment regarding the sauce - most restaurants do not use the flour/butter mixture. They use more liquids to start with, then reduce it over low/med heat until it is the desired thickness and add some butter to the sauce at the end to make it creamy. I only used 1/8 c lemon juice and 3/4 c white wine and reduced it over med heat by about 1/2 its original amount. I don't use capers so I did substitute some sauted mushrooms and served this over a bed of angel hair pasta and got major raves. I WILL definitely be doing this one again!

