Rating: 3
I have never written a review in 7 yrs of using this website, but I have to write one after reading others' reviews. Piccata IS lemony, by definition, tart and lively, not heavy, even refreshingly "cool." Secondly, mushrooms are earthy which does NOT mix with lemon. If you must add something to this recipe, try wilted, chopped spinach. Thirdly, garlic is NOT piccata; its flavor is too heavy and warming for this dish. Adding these ingredients may be good, but it is NOT piccata! My husband argues that angel hair is not an ideal pairing for this dish (although I disagree on this point), that a more substantial pasta like linguine or fettuccine soaks up less sauce and pairs better with the chicken. I agree with other reviews that the flour-butter roux is unnecessary, you must always rinse capers, the sauce must be added over the chicken at "plating," salt is the proper balance to tartness, and that with a good, unsalted broth the sauce can be stretched. We really like the Cook's Illustrated recipe for Chicken Piccata with its garnish of lemon slices.

