Rating: 3
I have been making this version of Chicken Piccata, a classic, since it was published in 1998. I have found over the years of making this recipe, that it depends on how old your lemons are to how tart the outcome will be. Older lemons are more tart than younger ones. I start with half a lemon and add as needed. You can use the amount given as a reference point. It's always easier to add more than try to compensate for adding to much, thats the beauty of cooking. As for the saltyness some reviewers experienced, it is the capers, a MUST in Chicken Piccata, that causes the salty flavor. The solution is to rinse them before adding to the pan, adding as it suits your taste.

